    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p><h2>Problem Statement</h2>\u00a0</p>\n\n<p> <font size=\"3\">Chef and his friend Devu are the heads of the sports club of their college.They have been given the responsibility to conduct the Inter-Department cricket tournament.There are n number of teams.Therefore inorder to estimate the total cost required they will have to find the minimum number of matches that are to be conducted if the each team plays with the other team exactly once.\n                                                                  <p> Moreover the top two teams in the league matches will play the finals.The cost of conducting each match is K rupees.</p></font>\n\n <p>  <font size=\"3\">Your task is to help them to find the estimated budget for the Tournament </font></p><p>\n</p>\n\n<h2>Input</h2>\n<p> <font size=\"3\">The first line contains two Integers n(no. of teams) and K(cost of conducting each match).</font></p>\n\n<h2>Output</h2>\n<p> <font size=\"3\">Estimated Budget Amount</font></p>\n\n<h2>Constraints</h2>\n <font size=\"3\"><p>2<=n<=10^6</p>\n<p>1<=k<=500</p></font>\n\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<b>Input:</b>\n<p> <font size=\"3\">5 20 </font></p>\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n <font size=\"3\"><p>220</p></font>\n\n<h2>Explanation</h2>\n<p> <font size=\"3\">There will be 11 total matches,so total estimated budget is 220 rupees  </font>..</p>",
